This paper deals with the problem of attributing advanced persistent threats (APTs) to specific nation-states or APT families. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) for classification and feature extraction, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning for reusing pre-trained models, and this falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of malware, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
